                  <h2>Ownership History</h2>
      <p>Purchased from the artist by Galerie Paul Guillaume, Paris, September 1926 (according to September 14, 1926 letter from Matisse to his wife, Amelie Matisse in archives Matisse, Paris, as cited in Spurling 2006, pp. 484–5, no. 1030); by descent to his wife, Juliette “Domenica” Lacaze  (later Mme. Jean Walter), Paris, 1934–summer 1951; sold to Henry and Rose Pearlman, New York, summer 1951–1953 [letter of December 4, 1975 from Rose Pearlman in curatorial file]; acquired through exchange by the Art Institute, 1953.</p>
